The paper proposes a deep learning model for multitask feature learning and image classification. The model is evaluated on multiple benchmark datasets, indicating a focus on machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the use of autoencoders and knowledge transfer, suggesting a possible fit for cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions image classification, which could also place it in the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category.
